---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="BuyerVoice.AI — The signal in the conversation"
  description="Buyer intelligence for growth-stage companies, built from hundreds of AI-moderated interviews and analyzed by a senior practitioner."
>
  <!-- Nav -->
  <nav class="nav">
    <div class="nav-inner">
      <a href="/" class="nav-logo" aria-label="BuyerVoice.AI home">
        <img src="/images/logo.svg" alt="BuyerVoice.AI" height="28" />
      </a>
      <a href="#contact" class="nav-cta">Request a briefing</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <!-- 1. Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="hero-headline">The signal in the conversation.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Buyer intelligence for growth-stage companies, built from hundreds of AI-moderated interviews and analyzed by a senior practitioner.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-rule"></div>
      <a href="#contact" class="cta-button">Request a briefing</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. The Problem -->
  <section class="section" id="problem">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">The problem</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Most companies don't understand how their buyers actually decide.</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Surveys capture what buyers will click. They rarely capture what buyers mean. A five-point scale tells you someone is "satisfied." It does not tell you why they almost switched to your competitor last quarter, or what phrase a colleague used that made them reconsider.
        </p>
        <p>
          Traditional interview research goes deeper, but a dozen conversations will not tell you how a market decides. You get anecdotes, not patterns. The research takes months and reads like an academic paper instead of a brief your team can act on Monday morning.
        </p>
        <p>
          Depth and scale have been a trade-off for a long time. They are not anymore.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- 3. Our Method -->
  <section class="section" id="method">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Our method</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Three steps. Hundreds of conversations. One clear answer.</h2>

      <div class="method-list">
        <div class="method-item">
          <span class="method-number">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="method-title">Interview at scale.</h3>
            <p>
              AI-moderated interviews run hundreds of structured conversations with buyers, switchers, and non-customers in your category. Each one follows a research-grade guide. Each one probes on follow-ups a survey never could.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="method-item">
          <span class="method-number">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="method-title">Anchor on the switch.</h3>
            <p>
              Every study centers on the buyer's last real decision in the category. What they considered, what they picked, what they regret. Switching analysis reveals the actual decision logic of your market, not a hypothetical ranking of features.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="method-item">
          <span class="method-number">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="method-title">Analyze with marketing science.</h3>
            <p>
              Transcripts are coded and analyzed using established frameworks: category entry points, jobs-to-be-done, perceived differentiation, switching cost models. The output is a structured finding, not a stack of highlighted quotes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- 4. What You Get -->
  <section class="section" id="deliverables">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">What you get</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">A finished answer, not a data dump.</h2>
      <p class="section-intro">
        Every engagement produces a set of deliverables designed to move directly into your marketing, product, and sales workflows. No dashboards. No raw transcripts dropped over the wall.
      </p>

      <div class="deliverables-list">
        <div class="deliverable">
          <h3>Narrative report</h3>
          <p>A structured account of how your market perceives your category, grounded in hundreds of real conversations. Written for executives, not academics.</p>
        </div>
        <hr class="rule-light" />
        <div class="deliverable">
          <h3>Switching map</h3>
          <p>A visual model of how buyers move between solutions in your category. What triggers consideration, what closes the deal, what causes regret.</p>
        </div>
        <hr class="rule-light" />
        <div class="deliverable">
          <h3>Persona-language library</h3>
          <p>The actual words your buyers use to describe their problems, evaluate alternatives, and justify decisions. Organized by persona and buying stage.</p>
        </div>
        <hr class="rule-light" />
        <div class="deliverable">
          <h3>Specific recommendations</h3>
          <p>Concrete actions for marketing, product, and sales, each tied to a finding in the data. Not "consider repositioning." Instead: here is the positioning, here is the evidence, here is who it resonates with.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="divider" />

  <!-- 5. Who's Behind It -->
  <section class="section" id="about">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Who's behind it</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Senior judgment on every engagement.</h2>

      <div class="about-grid">
        <div class="about-photo-wrap">
          <img src="/images/forest-baker.jpg" alt="Forest Baker, PhD" class="about-photo" />
        </div>
        <div class="about-bio">
          <h3>Forest Baker, PhD, MBA</h3>
          <p class="about-credentials">
            PhD in Experimental Psychology (judgment and decision making), SUNY Stony Brook. MBA in Market Analysis and Strategy, Duke Fuqua. NIDA Postdoctoral Fellow, University of Vermont. 2,200+ research citations.
          </p>
          <p>
            Nearly a decade at LinkedIn, where he designed and launched the platform's ad effectiveness measurement program and led a global insights team. Market research and product management at Abbott Vascular Devices, where he won the 2009 Marketing Award for new methods and significant insights.
          </p>
          <p>
            Top-performing account executive at Maze, a user research platform, where he closed the company's first $1M deal. His career spans academia, Fortune 500 research, and enterprise sales, which means he understands both the science behind buyer decisions and the business context in which those findings need to land.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Footer / Contact -->
  <footer class="footer" id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="footer-rule"></div>
      <div class="footer-content">
        <div>
          <img src="/images/logo.svg" alt="BuyerVoice.AI" height="24" class="footer-logo" />
          <p class="footer-tagline">Buyer intelligence, at interview depth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-contact">
          <p class="eyebrow">Get in touch</p>
          <a href="mailto:forest@buyervoice.ai" class="footer-email">forest@buyervoice.ai</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="footer-copy">&copy; 2026 BuyerVoice.AI. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Nav */
  .nav {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    z-index: 100;
    background: var(--paper);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(11, 31, 58, 0.08);
  }

  .nav-inner {
    max-width: var(--col-10);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
  }

  .nav-logo {
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .nav-cta {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
    border: 1.5px solid var(--ink);
    transition: background 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .nav-cta:hover {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding-top: clamp(140px, 20vw, 220px);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-gap);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: var(--col-8);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5.5vw, 3.6rem);
    line-height: 1.08;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    max-width: 14ch;
  }

  .hero-sub {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
  }

  .hero-rule {
    width: 60px;
    height: 2px;
    background: var(--signal);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .cta-button {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--paper);
    background: var(--ink);
    padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
    transition: background 0.15s ease;
  }

  .cta-button:hover {
    background: var(--signal);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    padding: var(--section-gap) 0;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.5vw, 2.2rem);
    line-height: 1.18;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }

  .section-intro {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: var(--measure);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .prose {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .prose p:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--ink);
    max-width: var(--col-8);
    margin: 0 auto;
    opacity: 0.12;
  }

  /* Method */
  .method-list {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2.5rem;
  }

  .method-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .method-number {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1;
    min-width: 48px;
    opacity: 0.15;
  }

  .method-title {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .method-item p {
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--rule);
  }

  /* Deliverables */
  .deliverables-list {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .deliverable {
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .deliverable h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .deliverable p {
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--rule);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .rule-light {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(11, 31, 58, 0.08);
  }

  /* About */
  .about-grid {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-photo-wrap {
    position: relative;
  }

  .about-photo {
    width: 180px;
    height: 220px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top center;
    filter: grayscale(100%);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .about-bio h3 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about-credentials {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .about-bio p {
    margin-top: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* Footer */
  .footer {
    padding: var(--section-gap) 0 3rem;
  }

  .footer-rule {
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .footer-content {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .footer-logo {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .footer-tagline {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .footer-contact {
    text-align: right;
  }

  .footer-email {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .footer-copy {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-photo {
      width: 140px;
      height: 170px;
    }

    .method-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .method-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .footer-content {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .footer-contact {
      text-align: left;
    }
  }
</style>
